ZH: 他今天又兴风作浪，把办公室搞得乱七八糟。
EN: He caused a disturbance again today, making a mess in the office.

ZH: 她总是在家里兴风作浪，让妈妈很生气。
EN: She always causes trouble at home, making her mother very angry.

ZH: 这个学生喜欢兴风作浪，老师总是得好好管教。
EN: This student likes to cause trouble, so the teacher always has to discipline him.

ZH: 小狗常常兴风作浪，把花园的花都毁了。
EN: The puppy often causes a mess, destroying all the flowers in the garden.

ZH: 如果你再这样兴风作浪，我就要报警了。
EN: If you keep causing trouble like this, I will have to call the police.

ZH: 我们不能容忍他们一直兴风作浪，必须采取行动。
EN: We cannot tolerate them causing trouble constantly, we must take action.

ZH: 再不收敛就要兴风作浪，别怪我不客气。
EN: If you don't behave better, I won't be polite when I cause trouble.

ZH: 他们兴风作浪的行为给整个社区带来了很多问题。
EN: Their disruptive behavior has caused a lot of problems for the whole community.

ZH: 小孩子们兴风作浪，把周围弄得一片狼藉。
EN: The children caused chaos all around, making a big mess.

ZH: 他们兴风作浪的举止让外人嘲笑。
EN: Their disruptive actions made them the target of ridicule by outsiders.

ZH: 这些抗议者兴风作浪，把街道都堵塞了。
EN: The protesters caused a commotion, blocking the streets.

ZH: 他们兴风作浪，惹恼了邻居。
EN: They caused trouble and annoyed the neighbors.

ZH: 不要再兴风作浪了，不然后果自负。
EN: Stop causing trouble, or you will face the consequences.

ZH: 那个人总是喜欢兴风作浪，引起不必要的麻烦。
EN: That person always likes to cause trouble and create unnecessary problems.

ZH: 他们的兴风作浪给公司造成了很大的损失。
EN: Their disruptive behavior has caused a lot of losses for the company.

ZH: 只有采取严厉措施，才能制止他们的兴风作浪。
EN: Only by taking strict measures can we stop their disruptive behavior.

ZH: 老师严厉地警告那些兴风作浪的学生。
EN: The teacher warned the troublemaking students sternly.

ZH: 这次游行兴风作浪，导致了冲突和混乱。
EN: The protest caused chaos, leading to conflict and confusion.

ZH: 假如你再兴风作浪，我就会报警。
EN: If you cause trouble again, I will call the police.

ZH: 这些暴徒兴风作浪，让整个城市陷入混乱。
EN: The rioters caused chaos, plunging the whole city into disorder.
